</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[189,1399,1251,1312]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[643,746,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collicola">
<emphasis box="[643,746,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">collicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘inhabitant of hills’ and referring to the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1399,1251,1277]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
locality on hills.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
