</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[189,1399,1821,2025]" lastBlockId="58.[189,1399,266,432]" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
HEAD. Face in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[513,620,1821,1847]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="58.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,491,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@58.[189,1399,491,1784]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="Fig. 21. Head, lateral view (A, D, F, J–K), dorsal view (B, C, G–H, L), frontal view (E, I). A–B. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. C. S. (A.) amplistylus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. D. S. (A.) apicalis Shiraki, 1930, ♀, Taiwan. E. S. (A.) bifida sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Sabah, Malaysia. F–G. S. (A.) bracon sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. H–I. S. (A.) bispinosa Brunetti, 1915, Ƌ, Nepal. J. S. (A.) brevipilis sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. K–L. S. (A.) collicola sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Malaysia. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830589/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 21K</figureCitation>
) concave, less projected antero-ventrally than frontal prominence; frontal prominence very weakly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 7.9; ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 1.1; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 3.7. Face black, light grey pollinose, long pilose along eye-margin. Hypostomal bridge black, long pale pilose. Gena and mouth edge black with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons and vertex black, velvet black pollinose, a narrow oval area posterior of lunula shiny non-pollinose and 2 squarish anterolateral grey pollinose macula along eye-margin (
<figureCitation box="[984,1094,266,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="58.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,491,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@58.[189,1399,491,1784]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="Fig. 21. Head, lateral view (A, D, F, J–K), dorsal view (B, C, G–H, L), frontal view (E, I). A–B. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. C. S. (A.) amplistylus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. D. S. (A.) apicalis Shiraki, 1930, ♀, Taiwan. E. S. (A.) bifida sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Sabah, Malaysia. F–G. S. (A.) bracon sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Vietnam. H–I. S. (A.) bispinosa Brunetti, 1915, Ƌ, Nepal. J. S. (A.) brevipilis sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. K–L. S. (A.) collicola sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Malaysia. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830589/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 21L</figureCitation>
); pile short, light yellow. Occiput black, light grey pollinose, light yellow pilose. Eye with an area of enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna with scape and pedicel black, basoflagellomere dark brown with several black setae dorsally on scape and pedicel; basoflagellomere oval, ratio width: length 1: 1.5; arista long pilose, about 2.5 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830589" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3830589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830589/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" startId="58.[189,232,1825,1851]" targetBox="[194,1398,491,1775]" targetPageId="58">
